<body style="background-color: #F7FBE1;">
    <!-- Schemes launced -->
    <div class="container px-4 py-5" id="featured-3">
        <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">Schemes launced by the Indian
            Government</h2>
        <br>
        <div
            class="row g-4 py-3 row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-3 b_d_background blurry_border">
            <div class="feature col">
                <div style="text-align: center;">
                    <img src="images/initiatives.png" alt
                        style="border: 1px solid black;">
                </div>
                <br>
                <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">FAME</h3>
                <p> Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of (Hybrid &) Electric
                    Vehicles
                    in India (FAME India) Scheme was launced in 2015. From 2019,
                    phase-II of this scheme has been implemented with an outlay
                    of
                    INR 10,000 Cr for a period of 5 years. Out of total
                    budgetary
                    support, about 86% of the fund has been allocated to create
                    demand for EVs in the country.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="feature col">
                <div style="text-align: center;">
                    <img src="images/initiatives.png" alt
                        style="border: 1px solid black;">
                </div>
                <br>
                <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">ACC</h3>
                <p> Scheme for National Programme on Advanced Chemistry Cell
                    (ACC)
                    Battery Storage was launched in 2021 to build and enhance
                    India's manufacturing capabilities in ACC domain with an
                    outlay
                    of INR 18,100 Cr for seven years. The second phase is yet to
                    be
                    launced.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="feature col">
                <div style="text-align: center;">
                    <img src="images/initiatives.png" alt
                        style="border: 1px solid black;">
                </div>
                <br>
                <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">PMP</h3>
                <p> Phased Manufacturing Programme has been introduced to
                    increase
                    the domestic
                    production of these vehicles in India. Under this programme
                    every section in the manufacturing of either vehicles or
                    it's parts will be given a seperate designated area with
                    proper
                    sequential following so that production can also be
                    increased
                    and cleanliness will also be maintained.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Initiatives taken -->
    <div class="container px-4 py-5" id="featured-3">
        <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">Initiatives taken by the Indian
            Government</h2>
        <div class="py-3 b_d_background blurry_border">
            <ul>
                <li> Every year on 9th September: World EV Day is conducted to
                    raise
                    awarness about the vehicles.</li>
                <li> GST on EVs and charging stations reduced from 12% to 5%.
                </li>
                <li> Interest Subvention: Discount offered on the interest rate
                    while availing loa. </li>
                <li> The Union Budget 2023-24 extended the customs duty
                    exemption to
                    the import of capital goods and machinery required for the
                    manufacture of lithium-ion cells for batteries used in
                    electric
                    vehicles. </li>
                <li> Both commercial as well as private battery-operated
                    vehicles
                    are given green licencse plates. </li>
                <li> To expand and strengthen the Public Electric Vehicle
                    Charging
                    Infrastructure across the nation, the Ministry of Power
                    issued
                    certain guildelines under which private players have
                    announced
                    of setting upto 22k EV charging stations in metro cities and
                    on
                    National Highways. </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

